article.description: Korey Billbury scored 18 of his 20 points in the first half and VCU routed Saint Louis 85-52 on Saturday night to snap a two-game skid.
article.headline: VCU routs Saint Louis 85-52, remains 1 game back in A-10
article.linkText: VCU routs Saint Louis 85-52, remains 1 game back in A-10
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- Korey Billbury scored 18 of his 20 points in the first half and VCU routed Saint Louis 85-52 on Saturday night to snap a two-game skid. The Rams (18-7, 10-2 Atlantic 10) have won 13 of their last 15 games and remain a game back of conference leader Dayton (21-3, 11-1), which beat Rhode Island on Friday. Billbury made four 3-pointers and was 8 of 11 from the field. Jonathan Williams added 12 points and matched a career-high with seven assists, and Justin Tillman had 12 points and 11 rebounds for the Rams, who shot 52 percent from the floor and had five in double-figure scoring. Jermaine Bishop scored 16 points to lead Saint Louis (8-16, 3-9), which has lost five straight. The Rams had a double-digit lead five minutes into the game, and led by 20 at halftime.
